  "prompt": "How can I watch the Shorty Awards on TV in the US?",
  "response": "The Shorty Awards are typically streamed online rather than broadcast on traditional television. However, here are a few ways you might be able to watch the Shorty Awards on a TV in the US:\n\n1. **Streaming Devices**: If you have a smart TV or a streaming device like Roku, Amazon Fire Stick, Apple TV, or Google Chromecast, you can access the Shorty Awards livestream through their website or social media platforms. Simply navigate to the Shorty Awards website or their official social media channels on the date of the event.\n\n2. **Screen Mirroring**: You can mirror your computer or mobile device screen to your TV. Most modern smart TVs support screen mirroring via AirPlay (for Apple devices) or Chromecast (for Android devices). Connect your device to the TV and play the Shorty Awards livestream from your browser or the Shorty Awards app.\n\n3. **HDMI Connection**: If your TV has an HDMI port, you can connect your laptop or computer to the TV using an HDMI cable. Open a web browser on your computer and navigate to the Shorty Awards livestream.\n\n4. **Social Media Platforms**: The Shorty Awards are often live-streamed on platforms like YouTube, Twitch, or Twitter (now known as X). If your TV has apps for these platforms, you can watch the livestream directly through those apps.\n\nTo stay updated on the specific date, time, and streaming details for the Shorty Awards, visit their official website or follow their social media accounts.",
